title: Grateful Dead Live at Richmond Coliseum on 1983-10-08
lineage: master cassette > cd > eac > flac; Transfer: sony tc-we435 > philips cdr870 Tracked in CDwave, FLACd Flac Frontend level 8 Tag & Rename for FLAC Meta-Tagging
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, West L.A. Fadeaway, Hell In A Bucket-> Deal

Set 2

Day Job-> Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Spoonful-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: A real Playin'>crazy fingers This is one of those shows when the setlist looks average but the music was anything but average.From the opening notes of stranger until the end of U.S. blues the energy was off the hook.Trust me on this.
Yeah what he said. Totally agree. I was there. And dosed some kickin Lucy. Whew. The end of DEAL IS SICK!!!!!!
- Excellent show, but I like the DaWeez version better.
